subject: Re: [junit] With out changing the excepted value in my code regularly
msgSnippet: ... Why does your expected result change frequently? Does it depend on the input or on some other dependency, like a database? Can you give me an example of
messageBody:
p_thanuja82 wrote:
>
>
> Hi All,
>
> In my test case the excepted value will be changed frequently.
> so I have to change my excepted data each and every time in my code. I
> dont want to go in to my code and change the excepted data.
>
> Instead of doing this, I want to get the data with out changing
> it every time. Please suggest me any other methods with out changing
> the excepted data in my code.

Why does your expected result change frequently? Does it depend on the
input or on some other dependency, like a database? Can you give me an
example of such a test?
